race.comment: Small field but some talented gallopers for this class of race. TI TREE LAD (2) looks one of the horses to beat. He is arguably the best horse in the race and he'll have to carry the weight accordingly. But he's drawn well and can stalk the speed. PRETENTIOUS LASS (7) will find this easier than last start and her win before that was full of merit. The map looks great for her and she's another who will be finishing hard late. SALSBURY HILL (4) is a last-start track and distance winner that must be respected, while ZEB'S GLASS (8) could be a horse to run a cheeky race at a price if things go his way.
